2	  A {@linkcode Result Result<T, E>} is a type representing the value result of a
3	  synchronous operation which may fail, with a successful value of type `T` or
4	  an error of type `E`.
5	
6	  If the result is a success, it is {@linkcode Ok Ok(value)}. If the result is a
7	  failure, it is {@linkcode Err Err(reason)}.
